    "Evolution of article content will also impact performance.",
    "We focus on two specific forms of such change: (1) due to spontaneous events, which we define as news-worthy happenings with a definite and narrow time-span, or (2) due to evolving topics, which we define as large, overarching collections of events that remain relatively static over a long period.",
    "Across these events and topics, we expect markedly different language.",
    "The distribution of publishers is also expected to change between training and inference time.",
    "All publishers exhibit some form of editorial bias or style, which can be memorized by classification models."
